    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen calling `nvim_close_win()` to close a window from another tab `T`, it closes all the tabs if the last window in `T` is a floating window.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean -u repro.lua`\n\nwere `repro.lua` is\n```lua\nlocal buffer = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false)\n\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(buffer, false, {\n  relative = \"editor\",\n  row = 0,\n  col = 0,\n  width = 1,\n  height = 1,\n})\n\nvim.cmd(\"tabnew\")\n\nvim.api.nvim_win_close(1000, false)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntab `T` should be closed, but it should not close the other tabs.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-278+g0741d2520d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim does not have the Lua API as far as I know\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nManjaro Linux 25.0.0\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.0 (53395536)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source with `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -j4`",
